<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.2.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-01-28T11:01:01-08:00</updated><id>/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Marty’s demo content</title><subtitle>This is a demonstration of markdown prowess.</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Soft-boiled eggs</title><link href="/recipes/2021/01/27/soft-boiled-eggs.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Soft-boiled eggs" /><published>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</updated><id>/recipes/2021/01/27/soft-boiled-eggs</id><content type="html" xml:base="/recipes/2021/01/27/soft-boiled-eggs.html">&lt;h3 id=&quot;ingredients&quot;&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 eggs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;instructions&quot;&gt;Instructions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Place eggs in a small saucepan with cold water.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Set the saucepan on medium-high heat until the water just starts to boil.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Turn the heat down to a low simmer and set a timer for 3 minutes.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;After 3 minutes, remove the eggs with a slotted spoon and plunge in cold water to stop the cooking.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Carefully crack and roll the eggs thoroughly before peeling.
If you’re making poached eggs for eggs benedict, try this quick recipe for [Hollandaise sauce].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tip:&lt;/strong&gt; If you eat boiled eggs frequently, consider a $15 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/Elite-Cuisine-EGC-007-Hard-Boiled-Auto-Shut/dp/B00F0RDRFS/&quot;&gt;egg steamer&lt;/a&gt;. If you buy &lt;em&gt;one&lt;/em&gt; single-use kitchen gadget, this is the one to get.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Marty Yu</name></author><category term="Recipes" /><summary type="html">Ingredients 2 eggs</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Fried eggs</title><link href="/recipes/2021/01/27/fried-egg.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fried eggs" /><published>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</updated><id>/recipes/2021/01/27/fried-egg</id><content type="html" xml:base="/recipes/2021/01/27/fried-egg.html">&lt;h3 id=&quot;ingredients&quot;&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;2 eggs&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;5 ml neutral cooking oil&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;salt&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;pepper&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;instructions&quot;&gt;Instructions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;On a medium stove burner, heat up a nonstick or well-seasoned cast iron pan.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add oil and swirl to evenly coat the bottom of the pan.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;As the oil starts to shimmer, crack the eggs into the pan.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; If the eggs spatter, reduce the heat.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;When the egg whites have set (3-4 minutes), use a spatula to gently plate the eggs.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Finish eggs with salt and pepper to taste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you prefer eggs over easy, check out the recipe over at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.seriouseats.com/recipes/2017/07/classic-over-easy-fried-eggs-recipe.html&quot;&gt;Serious Eats&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Marty Yu</name></author><category term="Recipes" /><summary type="html">Ingredients 2 eggs 5 ml neutral cooking oil salt pepper</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Function: Find a champion</title><link href="/functions/2021/01/27/hero-code.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Function: Find a champion" /><published>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-27T13:09:58-08:00</updated><id>/functions/2021/01/27/hero-code</id><content type="html" xml:base="/functions/2021/01/27/hero-code.html">&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;find_champion&lt;/code&gt; function to identify champions from a list of players:&lt;/p&gt;

